      "q": "How much does Department of Agriculture spend on contracts?",
      "a": "The Department of Agriculture spends $6.3B on contracts in FY2026 to date. That total covers 16,591 awards with an average award size of $382K, and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Obligations fell 33.8% year over year."
