    {
      "q": "What does Agriculture buy?",
      "a": "Agriculture buys transportation, construction, food processing, and IT services. Top NAICS categories in FY2026 to date include Nonscheduled Chartered Freight Air Transportation at $672M, Highway, Street, and Bridge Construction at $420M, Animal (except Poultry) Slaughtering at $406M, Fruit and Vegetable Canning at $392M, and Computer Systems Design Services at $309M."
